The radio beeped....

&quot;This is Celeron.... I&#39;ve located a prisoner, and he&#39;s quite agitated.  Requesting backup....&quot;

&quot;.............This is Tigon, I&#39;m going to get some detention equipment, try to keep him busy.  The captain is regenerating.  You&#39;re on your own.&quot;

&quot;.....Rodger......&quot;

Ironically, the prisoner had already broken out of the pod and was 9 inches from his face when he turned around.

Celeron stared down the barrel of two high caliber energy pistols.  Four seconds later, Celeron had been blown back 600 yards.

&quot;Armor 20%.....&quot;  said his onboard computer.

Celeron charged up the cannon on his right arm and steadied it with his left.  Once he got a lock on the prisoner who was rapidly closing on him, he fired and blew it back about half as far as he had been blown back.  Celeron realizing that he&#39;s out matched began to run.

The prisoner had full flight capability and as they flew around for a while Celeron discovered that it was also well armed.

&quot;Armor at 10%.......Target at estimated 75%&quot; read the computer.

&quot;Arrrgggg!&quot; Celeron grunted as he attacked.

&quot;{Bleep}  Celeron....I have the equipment, I&#39;ll be out there ASAP....standby.&quot;

